  "text": "Effects of fucoidan fractions from brown algae of L. saccharina on bFGF-mediated angiogenesis bFGF is an essential mediator capable of regulating angiogenesis [CITATION_1] . We examined whether the parent fucoidan from L. saccharina or its fractions could selectively modulate bFGF-mediated events. We initially investigated the effect of such polysaccharides by targeting bFGF-induced HUVEC tubulogenesis For such assay, each polysaccharide and bFGF were added before plating HUVEC onto Matrigel. As shown in Figure 4A -B, addition of 100 mg/ml parent fucoidan from L. saccharina (L.s.-P) or the L.s.-1.25 fraction blocked (99% inhibition, P,0.001) bFGF-induced HUVEC tube formation, while L.s.-1.0 had no effect.",
